reviewText: I want my hour back that I wasted on this stupid movie.
good movie
Sometimes I had a  little trouble  following the  plot but did enjoy the movie. Really liked the  ending.

A slight twist to the 'trip to the woods to be sad for someone' flick. The forest setting / action was a little strained and predictable. However, it was just a hub for what I consider the 'real' movie. And that's where I thought they did a good job filling in backstory in pieces as the forest drama was unfolding.

Don't understand the one star reviews. Ok so it has some issues, like actors that were not so great.  At least the "friends in the woods with a murderer" theme was your the standard one.  A lot of the film was back story told via flash-backs and it was at least enough to stay interested.  Quite a twisted tale indeed!

This is a good thriller. It has great suspense and action throughout. The characters are believable and interesting. Even though the movie is told mostly in flashbacks, it helped to unravel the mystery and resolve this whodunit type of movie. There were a couple of loose ends that were not explained such as the why one of the main characters was targeted to begin with. But overall, a clever and suspenseful thriller.

Oh my gosh, this was so confusing.  There are flashbacks, flash forwards, flash sidewards and maybe an upside down one. Adultery, prostitution, murder and even all of that wasn't enough to save this movie

This is a pretty decent movie in my opinion. I've seen better, but I've also seen MUCH WORSE. The plot was interesting, and I think the acting is good. It doesn't seem low budget to me. Was definitely worth a watch.
Low quality.  BTDT script.  Weak acting. Need I say more?
Ok

This movie was a waste of time. Not only It was a crappy movie, it arrived at my house, supposedly a new tape, it had no shrink wrap and was held closed with a single strip of scotch tape. The cover art on the case was a bad copy and to top it off it was shipped loose in the case. It was even on a DVR instead of a regular DVD. Save your money, save your time and get a different movie altogether.
IMDB shows this was released in 2012, not 2015. It had an $80K Budget. That is really all that needs to be said. You have been warned!
